id="post-3628" class="post-3628 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-direct-action category-environment category-food-body-mind tag-beer tag-butterfly tag-pelican-pub-brewery"><h2 class="entry-title"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2013/01/23/a-beer-for-butterflies/" title="Permalink to A Beer for Butterflies" rel="bookmark">A Beer for Butterflies</a></h2><div
class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2013/01/23 10:51 am"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2013/01/23/a-beer-for-butterflies/" title="A Beer for Butterflies" rel="bookmark">2013/01/23 10:51 am</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/administrator/" title="by Adam Clare" rel="author">Adam Clare</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p>Beer is delicious so it&#8217;s exciting to find out that at least one brewery is out there using their delvious suds to help a threatened species. <a
href="http://www.yourlittlebeachtown.com/pelican">Pelican Pub &#038; Brewery</a> in Oregon are using profits from one of their beers to fund the protection of butterflies from encroaching development and invasive species.</p><blockquote><p>Now we have the newish Silverspot IPA, introduced last summer by the Pelican Pub &#038; Brewery of Pacific City, Oregon. Downing one of these English-style IPAs will help efforts to increase populations of the threatened Oregon Silverspot Butterfly.</p><p>Once fairly common in northwest grasslands, the OSB (Speyeria zerene Hippolyta) became the victim of lost habitat, in terms of the early blue violet plant, also known as the dog violet (Viola adunca). It’s the great chain of ecological being—muck with this species here, and that species over there suffers as well.</p><p>The butterfly lays its eggs near the plant, which then serves as the sole source of food for the growing caterpillars.</p></blockquote><p><a
href="http://tombedell.com/golf/golf/lifestyle/3901/tap-beer-of-the-week-silverspot-ipa/">Read more here.</a></p><p><a
href="http://beerology.ca">Thanks to Mirella!</a></p><div
class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-1111807-3628-53836e546ba6a' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/#blog_id=1111807&amp;post_id=3628&amp;origin=www.thingsaregood.com&amp;obj_id=1111807-3628-53836e546ba6a' data-name='like-post-frame-1111807-3628-53836e546ba6a'><h3 class='sd-title'>Like this:</h3><div
